.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-SECMARKS 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-secmarks \- SELinux security mark labelling (configuration accepted, not emitted)
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I secmarks
file is accepted by the shorewall-nft parser for configuration compatibility
with classic Shorewall.
.B No nft output is emitted for this file in the current release.

In classic Shorewall,
.I secmarks
labels connections with SELinux security marks
.RB ( secmark )
for use with SELinux Mandatory Access Control policies.  shorewall-nft does
not currently implement secmark emit paths.

If you rely on secmark functionality, continue to use classic Shorewall for
that aspect of your policy, or open an issue in the project tracker.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/secmarks
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).

The file is parsed but ignored.  Columns for reference:

.TS
l l l.
Column	Description
_
SECMARK	SELinux security context string
CHAIN	Chain to label in
SOURCE	Source zone:address or CIDR
DEST	Destination zone:address or CIDR
PROTO	Protocol filter
DPORT	Destination port filter
SPORT	Source port filter
STATE	Connection state filter
.TE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)

.SH AUTHOR
André Valentin <avalentin@marcant.net>

.SH BUGS
